      "text": "Miguel Solis-Martinez, of Honduras, was arrested in 2008 for soliciting someone to murder his spouse in Bexar County, Texas. He was sentenced to a decade behind bars.\n\n🔎Solis snuck into the country in 1999 near San Ysidro, Calif., and was put into removal proceedings. An immigration judge granted him voluntary departure in 2002 — in other words, he agreed to leave the country on his own rather than get deported. He didn’t leave though.\n\nIn addition to the homicide-related conviction, his rap sheet also includes:\n➡️Illegal re-entry conviction\n➡️Forgery charge\n➡️DUI arrest",
